<Base
  title="Chatwork vs Slack for Japan Teams: Honest Comparison - MKUltraman"
  description="Chatwork vs Slack for Japan teams - pricing, Japanese SaaS integrations, UI/UX differences, and when each platform actually makes sense for your business."
  article={true}
  pubDate={pubDate}
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="compare">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="compare-article">
        <header class="compare-header">
          <a href="/compare/" class="back-link">← All comparisons</a>
          <span class="compare-eyebrow">Comparison · Last verified {lastVerified}</span>
          <h1>Chatwork vs Slack for Japan Teams</h1>
          <p class="compare-lead">
            Two business chat platforms. Both claim to be the modern alternative
            to email. Neither is universally right. Here's the honest breakdown:
            pricing, Japanese SaaS integration reality, adoption friction, and when
            each platform actually makes sense.
          </p>
          <div class="compare-meta">
            <span>By <a href="/about/" rel="author">Matt Ketchum</a></span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>Tokyo</span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>~8 min read</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <aside class="tldr" aria-label="Verdict summary">
          <h2 class="tldr__heading">Verdict</h2>
          <div class="verdict">
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>Chatwork wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Japanese-first teams</li>
                <li>SMEs under 50 people</li>
                <li>Cost-sensitive deployments</li>
                <li>Businesses already in the Japanese SaaS ecosystem (Kintone, freee, SmartHR)</li>
                <li>Non-technical users who need simple adoption</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>Slack wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>International or bilingual teams</li>
                <li>Heavy integration needs (Jira, GitHub, Notion, Zapier)</li>
                <li>Developer-first organizations</li>
                <li>Businesses with remote-first English-speaking culture</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="verdict__conclusion">
            For domestic Japanese teams under 50 people, <strong>Chatwork is the default right answer</strong>.
            For international teams or any org where integrations drive workflow, Slack earns its cost premium.
          </p>
        </aside>

        <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
          <h2 class="toc__heading">On this page</h2>
          <ol class="toc__list">
            <li><a href="#at-a-glance">At a glance</a></li>
            <li><a href="#pricing">Pricing in Japan (real numbers)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#chatwork-dominates">Why Chatwork dominates Japanese SMEs</a></li>
            <li><a href="#slack-wins">When Slack is the right call</a></li>
            <li><a href="#japan-factors">Japan-specific factors</a></li>
            <li><a href="#alternatives">Alternatives worth considering</a></li>
            <li><a href="#decision-framework">Decision framework</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq">Frequently asked questions</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <section id="at-a-glance" class="compare-section">
          <h2>At a glance</h2>
          <div class="compare-table-wrap">
            <table class="compare-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>&nbsp;</th>
                  <th>Chatwork</th>
                  <th>Slack</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
